Bah.  H. CotC, I hereby Call for Judgement on the following statement:

     Rule 1513 should be interpreted such that, if a body of text has
     been read by a Player, then it shall not lack the power to require
     that Player to perform or not perform an action solely because the
     Rules fail to require that it be made available to that Player.

Caller's Arguments:

Rule 1513 ends with this text:

     Especially, no body of text is permitted to require Players to
     perform or not perform any actions unless said body of text has
     previously been made available to that Player.

This says "Text T can bind Player P only if P has read T"; it does not
say "Text T can bind Player P only if the Rules require that P can
receive a copy of T".

